# 7. Texture sets and surface identities

Keep these concepts separate:

```text
Texture recipe:
How pixels are generated.

Texture set:
The baked albedo, normal-height, and ORM layers.

Surface:
How the texture behaves in the world.

Classifier rule:
Where the surface should appear.
```

Multiple surfaces can reuse one texture set.

For example:

```text
surface.dry_basalt
surface.cave_basalt
surface.wave_polished_basalt
```

could all use:

```text
texture.basalt
```

but apply different scales, roughness offsets, overlay responses, and classifier rules.

