# 9. Preventing visible biome bands

Biome and elevation rules can produce contour-shaped material borders.

Add low-amplitude spatial variation to thresholds:

```text
effective threshold =
base threshold
+ regional variation
+ local variation
```

But use the noise only to disturb a valid transition.

Bad:

```text
Noise chooses whether this is forest soil or snow.
```

Better:

```text
Elevation and climate establish the snow transition.
Noise makes the boundary irregular.
```

Example:

```rust
let transition_offset =
    macro_noise.sample(world_xz * 0.003) * 0.08
    + detail_noise.sample(world_xz * 0.025) * 0.025;

let adjusted_snow_score =
    snow_score + transition_offset;
```

