# 12. Bevy material definition

Bevy’s official array-texture example binds a `texture_2d_array` through `AsBindGroup` and samples a selected array layer while reusing Bevy’s PBR lighting functions. That is the right foundation for this terrain material. ([Bevy][3])

```rust
use bevy::{
    prelude::*,
    reflect::TypePath,
    render::render_resource::{
        AsBindGroup,
        ShaderType,
    },
    shader::ShaderRef,
};

const TERRAIN_SHADER: &str =
    "terrain_materials/shaders/terrain_pbr.wgsl";

#[derive(Clone, Copy, Debug, ShaderType)]
pub struct TerrainMaterialUniform {
    pub layer_indices: UVec4,
    pub meters_per_repeat: Vec4,
    pub normal_strengths: Vec4,

    pub triplanar_sharpness: f32,
    pub height_blend_strength: f32,
    pub macro_variation_scale: f32,
    pub macro_variation_strength: f32,
}

#[derive(Asset, TypePath, AsBindGroup, Debug, Clone)]
pub struct TerrainMaterial {
    #[texture(0, dimension = "2d_array")]
    #[sampler(1)]
    pub albedo_array: Handle<Image>,

    #[texture(2, dimension = "2d_array")]
    #[sampler(3)]
    pub normal_height_array: Handle<Image>,

    #[texture(4, dimension = "2d_array")]
    #[sampler(5)]
    pub orm_array: Handle<Image>,

    #[uniform(6)]
    pub settings: TerrainMaterialUniform,
}

impl Material for TerrainMaterial {
    fn fragment_shader() -> ShaderRef {
        TERRAIN_SHADER.into()
    }
}
```

Register it:

```rust
pub struct TerrainMaterialPlugin;

impl Plugin for TerrainMaterialPlugin {
    fn build(&self, app: &mut App) {
        app.add_plugins(
            MaterialPlugin::<TerrainMaterial>::default(),
        );
    }
}
```

