# 13. Texture-array organization

Use one corresponding layer number across all arrays:

```text
Layer 0:
soil albedo
soil normal-height
soil ORM

Layer 1:
basalt albedo
basalt normal-height
basalt ORM

Layer 2:
sand albedo
sand normal-height
sand ORM
```

All array layers must use compatible:

```text
Dimensions
Mip count
Pixel format
Array-layer count
Sampling assumptions
```

Assign array-layer indices deterministically:

```text
Sort compiled texture-set IDs
Assign indices in sorted order
Write manifest
```

Never let load order determine array indices.

## Manifest

```yaml
schema_version: 1
catalog_hash: "0cd7..."

layers:
  texture.beach_sand: 0
  texture.rainforest_soil: 1
  texture.river_mud: 2
  texture.weathered_basalt: 3
```

Bevy supports interpreting a vertically stacked image as a two-dimensional array texture through `ImageArrayLayout`, which is useful for prototyping. ([Bevy][3])

Production builds should preferably use a dedicated bake step that constructs the array assets and mip chains before shipping.

