    pub scorch: f32,
    pub mud: f32,
}
```

## Wetness

Wetness can:

```text
Darken albedo
Reduce roughness
Reduce porous normal detail
Increase specular response
Create pooled-water effects in cavities
```

## Moss

Moss can depend on:

```text
Moisture
Shade
Surface orientation
Rainfall
Rock porosity
Distance from ocean spray
Time undisturbed
```

## Snow or ash

Snow and ash can depend on:

```text
Upward-facing normal
Temperature or eruption state
Wind exposure
Slope
Shelter
Accumulation history
```

## Scorch and damage

Localized effects should normally use:

```text
Decals
Sparse surface patches
Persistent voxel or surface-state deltas
```

Do not permanently rebake the entire basalt texture because one part of one chunk burned.

---

# 19. Overlay storage for volumetric terrain

A global X/Z overlay map will not work for caves.

Use one of these approaches:

### Per-vertex overlay attributes

Best for effects that update when the chunk remeshes:

```text
Wetness
Moss potential
Snow retention
Weathering
```

### Sparse surface-patch records

Best for localized persistent effects:

```text
Scorch
Blood
Acid damage
Oil
Paint
Localized mud
```

### Decals

Best for short-lived or sharply bounded visual effects.

### Voxel-associated state

Best when the effect is tied to material simulation:

```text
Burned material
Saturated soil
Frozen water
Corroded structure
```

When a chunk remeshes, voxel state is converted into vertex overlay values.

