# 20. Asset loading

Define your catalog as a custom Bevy asset.

```rust
#[derive(Asset, TypePath, Debug)]
pub struct TerrainMaterialCatalogAsset {
    pub definition: TerrainMaterialCatalogDefinition,
}
```

Loader shape:

```rust
use bevy::asset::{
    io::Reader,
    AssetLoader,
    LoadContext,
};

pub struct TerrainMaterialCatalogLoader;

impl AssetLoader for TerrainMaterialCatalogLoader {
    type Asset = TerrainMaterialCatalogAsset;
    type Settings = ();
    type Error = TerrainCatalogError;

    async fn load(
        &self,
        reader: &mut dyn Reader,
        _settings: &Self::Settings,
        _load_context: &mut LoadContext<'_>,
    ) -> Result<Self::Asset, Self::Error> {
        let mut bytes = Vec::new();
        reader.read_to_end(&mut bytes).await?;

        let definition =
            serde_yaml_ng::from_slice(&bytes)?;

        validate_catalog(&definition)?;

        Ok(TerrainMaterialCatalogAsset {
            definition,
        })
    }

    fn extensions(&self) -> &[&str] {
        &["material_catalog.yaml"]
    }
}
```

Bevy’s `AssetLoader` loads assets asynchronously from a `Reader`, and `LoadContext` tracks asset dependencies. This allows a catalog loader to record dependencies on referenced texture recipes, surface definitions, and palettes. ([Docs.rs][4])

---

# 21. Catalog compilation

Raw YAML should not be used directly during terrain generation.

Compile it first:

```rust
pub struct CompiledSurfaceRegistry {
    pub surfaces: Vec<CompiledSurface>,
    pub surface_by_id:
        BTreeMap<SurfaceId, SurfaceIndex>,

    pub texture_layers:
        BTreeMap<TextureSetId, u32>,

    pub classifiers:
        BTreeMap<ClassifierId, CompiledClassifier>,

    pub palettes:
        BTreeMap<PaletteId, CompiledPalette>,
}
```

Compilation should:

```text
Resolve string IDs
Check references
Assign numeric indices
Compile scoring curves
Topologically sort texture graphs
Precompute constants
Calculate content hashes
Identify required texture outputs
Assign array layers
Build dependency indexes
```

The runtime classifier should not search strings or parse YAML.

---

# 22. Texture bake cache

Cache generated textures by content hash.

```text
hash =
texture recipe
+ generator version
+ resolution
+ channel packing
+ color space
+ mip settings
```

Suggested cache layout:

```text
cache/
  procedural_textures/
    11a408.../
      albedo.bin
      normal_height.bin
      orm.bin
      metadata.yaml
```

Metadata:

```yaml
recipe: texture.weathered_basalt
recipe_hash: "11a408..."
generator_version: 4
resolution: [512, 512]
mip_levels: 10
channels:
  albedo: srgb
  normal_height: linear
  orm: linear
```

When the recipe hash matches, reuse the cached result.

When it does not, rebuild only that texture set and any dependent texture arrays.

