# 26. Performance controls

## Limit active material samples

Even if a region supports eight surfaces:

```text
Sort weights per fragment or vertex
Select strongest four
Ignore negligible weights
Normalize selected weights
```

## Rendering quality profiles

```yaml
schema_version: 1
id: render.terrain_high

active_layers: 4
projection: triplanar
projection_axes: 3

normal_mapping: true
height_blending: true
macro_variation: true

distance_lod:
  - maximum_distance_m: 80
    active_layers: 4
    projection_axes: 3

  - maximum_distance_m: 240
    active_layers: 2
    projection_axes: 2

  - maximum_distance_m: 800
    active_layers: 1
    projection_axes: 1

  - maximum_distance_m: infinity
    active_layers: 1
    normal_mapping: false
```

## Channel packing

Use:

```text
One normal-height sample
One ORM sample
One albedo sample
```

rather than separate textures for every scalar channel.

## Reduce distant detail

At distance:

```text
Disable height blending
Reduce normal strength
Use dominant-axis projection
Use only the strongest material
Rely more heavily on macrovariation
```

